# i18n and Errors

## Exception keys

`I18nExceptionFilter` (`src/common/filters/i18n-exception.filter.ts`) translates exception messages via `Accept-Language`.

Always throw keys like `'PHONE_EXISTS'`, `'INVALID_CREDENTIALS'`, `'NO_QUOTA_OR_CREDITS'`.

## Translation files

Add keys to matching namespaces in **both** locales:

- `src/i18n/en/*.json`
- `src/i18n/ar/*.json`

Namespaces: `auth`, `common`, `errors`, `listing`, `subscription`, `user`, `todo`, `note`, `notification`.

## Response translation

Global interceptors in `src/main.ts` translate successful response fields:

- `TranslateInterceptor` — request-side field mapping
- `ResponseTranslateInterceptor` — response-side translation

Use `@UseInterceptors(TranslateInterceptor)` on endpoints returning translatable catalog data (listings, cities, property types).
